§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Sometimes it is convenient to partition the set of veritices
    of a graph. ⦉
⦉

§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Given a directed graph $G = (V, E)$, a ❬marking❭ (or
    ❬coloring❭) of $G$ is a partition $P$ of $V$. ⦉

  ‖ A ❬marked graph❭ (or ❬colored graph❭) is a pair $(G, M)$
    where $M$ is a marking for $G$. ⦉
⦉

